with someone else.

09:07.667 --> 09:10.208
So, Susan,
is he gonna stop seeing that woman?

09:13.458 --> 09:15.458
I don't know.

09:18.834 --> 09:21.291
I'm sorry, you guys, I just...

09:23.458 --> 09:25.959
I just don't know
how I'm gonna survive this.

09:27.500 --> 09:29.125
Listen to me.

09:29.250 --> 09:31.792
We all have moments of desperation.

09:33.583 --> 09:37.750
If we can face them head-on, that's when
we find out how strong we really are.

09:44.333 --> 09:45.667
Susan.

09:47.083 --> 09:49.917
I was just saying
Paul wants us to go over on Friday.

09:50.000 --> 09:52.625
He needs us to help
pack up Mary Alice's things.

09:52.709 --> 09:54.542
He can't face doing it by himself.

09:54.625 --> 09:58.500
- Sure. That's fine.
- Are you OK?

09:58.583 --> 10:02.417
Yeah. I'm just so angry.

10:02.500 --> 10:06.750
If Mary Alice was having problems,
she should've let us help her.

10:06.834 --> 10:09.709
What problems could she have had?
She was healthy,

10:09.834 --> 10:12.375
had a great home, a nice family.
Her life was...

10:12.458 --> 10:14.625
Our life.

10:16.500 --> 10:19.667
No. If Mary Alice was having a crisis,
we'd have known.

10:19.750 --> 10:21.834
